	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Some facts about this spell:<BR>
<BR>
#1 This spell does 220 + lvl-39 damage on the way up, and 100 points of falling damage to NPCs. Size, type, and terrain do not change the amount of damage it does.<BR>
<BR>
#2 This spell costs an insane amount of mana. 335 i believe, or very close to that. I doubt there are namy spells past lvl 20 that cost more mana than damage it does. I could be wrong )<BR>
<BR>
#3 WHY THIS IS A GOOD SPELL: This is the first, last, and only AE nuke for enchanters. On that note, it does have a much lower hate aggro than other enchanter nukes. You can use this spell on a HG and it &quot;might&quot; not come after you, instead of &quot;definately will&quot; come after you after casting Anarchy.<BR>
  The third and best plus for this spell is the fact that it is Alteration, not Evocation. Any enchanter that didnt specialize in Alteration isnt worth his illusions if you ask me, and since I did specialize in Alteration, Ive got a pretty good chance of cutting the mana cost in half everytime i use it.<BR>
<BR>
So there you have it. Its on OK and very fun spell. But it isnt great. But hey, you shouldnt be nuking much in combat anyways, so quit your crying ;)<BR>
<BR>
Halx Quixotic<BR>
Keeper of Order<BR>
Candiria Knights<BR>
Torvonillous
				</font>
